<center><font size=7><b>Knight Lore</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 5</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>His
news is that you need to put
fourteen items in the cauldron
and it doesn't matter how many
rooms you visit in the castle.
 <i>(Ian Pullen in Your Spectrum issue 16)</i> 

<br><hr>
<B>David Bass</B> from Bridgwater,
for example, suggests that you
never go near the wizard when
you're a werewolf. He's also
worked out that the bouncing
balls aim straight for the wolf
but avoid Sabreman, so it's best
to lay low when you've turned
into a wolf.
 <i>(David Bass in Your Spectrum issue 17)</i> 

<br><hr>
The
basic principle of the game
being to put the Seven Charms
into the Wizard's Cauldron,
<I>in order</I>: <BR>
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bottle, Sphere, Chalice,
Bottle, Diamond, Sphere,
Poison, Boot, Cup, Diamond,
Poison, Boot, Chalice, Cup. <BR>
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;	As <B>Simon Robinson</B> of
Enfield tells me, &quot;The list
would be better drawn in a
circle, as the first object
required may be any one of
them. Once you know your
position in the list, you can
proceed with confidence.&quot;
 <i>(Simon Robinson, Unknown in Your Spectrum issue 19)</i> 

<br><hr>
<a href="http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~jimg/yr19/yr19_64.htm">http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~jimg/yr19/yr19_64.htm</a>&nbsp; <i>(Simon Robinson, Unknown in Your Spectrum issue 19)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Infinite Lives</td><td>53567,0 </td></tr>
<tr><td>Infinite Days</td><td>50208,126</td></tr>
<tr><td>Stops Sundial</td><td>50084,201</td></tr>
<tr><td>Objects = x</td><td>49759,x (x= 1-255)</td></tr>
</table>
<BR>For the "Objects=x" POKE, only put in a SMALLER amount of objects to collect, as the game only generates a set amount
of objects at set locations.. Don't take my word for it though.. I was always crap at this game....
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
